    "title": [
      "[Northern Slopes, Rocky Incline]"
    ],
    "description": [
      "The precarious path down the steep face of the bluff levels off briefly, forming a small ledge with dangerously unstable edges.  Wind whips by, buffeting the precipice with sleet and snow.  Lodged pitifully in a pile of boulders next to the sheer rock face lies the carcass of an antelope.  Its limbs are broken across the granite, and little more than a pile of hide and protruding bones remains of the graceful creature, mute testament to the brutality of the region."
    ],
